<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,576,727]" lastBlockId="3.[113,1090,219,819]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="198" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,576,599]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The only extant species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1831" box="[554,708,576,599]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Leptomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,708,576,599]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Leptomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following combination of characters: male antennae covered in long setae (unique in the genus); yellow V-shaped marking on the dorsal side of dark brown scutum; katepisternum yellow and brown; metakatepisternum partially dark brown; abdominal segments swelling towards the apex of terminalia. Sternite 9 with medioventral lobe and a pair of lateroventral lobes bearing four dark megasetae apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,321,219,243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[258,314,219,243]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[462,560,220,243]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="14.3">14.3 mm</quantity>
. General colouration dark brown and dark yellow, yellow-orange and brown striped abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[586,677,252,275]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1477,1496]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,777,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[151,1126,774,1456]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov.: 1 – male (Photo: J. Ševčík); 2 – female (Photo: J. Ševčík); 3 – male, habitus; 4 – female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315592/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 1, 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315592" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5315592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315592/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" startId="2.[151,188,1477,1496]" targetBox="[151,1126,777,1456]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,1477,1522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
Figs 1–4. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab, 2017" authorityName="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab" authorityYear="2017" box="[240,429,1477,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Leptomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sevciki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[240,429,1477,1496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Leptomorphus sevciki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[436,508,1477,1496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 1 – male (Photo: J. Ševčík); 2 – female (Photo: J. Ševčík); 3 – male, habitus; 4 – female, habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1090,219,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis box="[144,202,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown, light brown laterally with many long setae. Ocelli yellow, in a straight line. Face yellow. Flagellomeres dark brown, densely covered with long, fine, dark brown setae (
<figureCitation box="[184,251,348,371]" captionStart="Figs 5–8. 5–7" captionStartId="3.[112,149,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-253@3.[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. 5–7 – Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov., male: 5 – antennae; 6 – thorax, V-shape mark; 7 – wing; 8 – female, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315594/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Basal part of first flagellomere yellow. Scape and pedicel yellow, setae on at least the anterior surface. Face and clypeus covered with many long setae. Clypeus and palpus light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1090,219,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis box="[144,228,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Thorax.</emphasis>
Mostly dark brown. Scutum dark brown with dorsal yellow V-shape marking, covered with fine hairs, several long light setae along margin (
<figureCitation box="[764,828,476,499]" captionStart="Figs 5–8. 5–7" captionStartId="3.[112,149,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-253@3.[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. 5–7 – Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov., male: 5 – antennae; 6 – thorax, V-shape mark; 7 – wing; 8 – female, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315594/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Scutellum light brown, with many short setae. Antepronotum, proepisternum, anepisternum, anepimeron and laterotergite dark brown. Proepisternum covered with light setae. Paratergite light to dark brown. Laterotergite with several long setae. Anepisternum and anepimeron bare. Katepisternum anterior dark brown and posterior yellow, bare. Metakatepisternum partially dark brown, bare. Mediotergite yellow, bare. Margin of anterior and posterior spiracles yellow with yellow trichia. Haltere: stem yellow, knob dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1090,219,819]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="199" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis box="[144,199,700,723]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[211,274,700,723]" captionStart="Figs 5–8. 5–7" captionStartId="3.[112,149,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-253@3.[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. 5–7 – Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov., male: 5 – antennae; 6 – thorax, V-shape mark; 7 – wing; 8 – female, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315594/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, membrane densely covered with irregularly arranged macrotrichia. Cell among base of R1, crossvein r-m and M bare, sector between veins M and CuA bare except apically. Apical shading dark brown but fading towards apex and posterior margin (pale brown apical wing shading not reaching to wing tip), running from anterior to posterior wing margin, beginning halfway along R5. Medial macula small, only around Rs. Costa ending at tip of R5. Sc short, ending in costa beyond base of r-m. Vein sc-r ending beyond Rs. Vein R4 absent. Vein R5 slightly concave for entire length. Crossvein r-m relatively long (twice as long as radial sector). Apex of crossvein r-m lighter than base. Apices of M and CuA veins clearly reaching wing margin. Point of furcation of CuA and M4 well before crossvein r-m. CuP thick, slightly shorter than A
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315594" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5315594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315594/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" startId="3.[112,149,1541,1560]" targetBox="[115,1083,871,1529]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[112,1089,1541,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
Figs 5–8. 5–7 – 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab, 2017" authorityName="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab" authorityYear="2017" box="[250,436,1541,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Leptomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sevciki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[250,436,1541,1560]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Leptomorphus sevciki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[441,509,1541,1560]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 5 – antennae; 6 – thorax, V-shape mark; 7 – wing; 8 – female, genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" box="[507,515,396,410]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">1</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" box="[515,546,380,403]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">. A</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" box="[546,554,396,410]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">1</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" box="[561,647,380,403]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">distinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,531]" lastBlockId="5.[113,1089,220,1299]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis box="[181,238,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxae principally yellow, forecoxa dark brown and hind coxa with anterior dark brown mark. All trochanters brown. Femora yellow, dark long setae laterally, hind femur brownish, dense setulae and dark brown mark beginning one third of length of hind femur and reaching beyond midpoint. Fore tibia yellow with basal brown mark, dense row of anteroventral bristles absent. Mid tibia entirely dark brown with irregular rows of short dark bristles. Hind tibia yellow with basal dark brown mark longer than fore tibia basal mark. Tarsi dark brown. First and second hind tarsomeres yellowish to light brown with dark brown apex.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315598" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5315598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315598/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="199" startId="4.[150,187,1490,1509]" targetBox="[303,970,561,1479]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[150,1129,1490,1589]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">
Figs 9–12 – 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab, 2017" authorityName="Kaspřák &amp; Borkent &amp; Wahab" authorityYear="2017" box="[253,437,1490,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Leptomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sevciki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[253,437,1490,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">Leptomorphus sevciki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[441,508,1490,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male, terminalia: 9 – ventral part, internal view; 10 – ventral part, external view; 11 – dorsal part, internal view; 12 – dorsal part, external view. Abbreviations: cerc = cercus; ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; epi = epiproct; gst = gonostylus; hyp = hypoproct; mvl st 9 = medioventral lobe of sternite 9; lvl st 9 = lateroventral lobe of sternite 9; par = paramere; par ap = parameral apodeme; st 9 = sternite 9; tg 9 = tergite 9.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,220,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis box="[144,252,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites principally dark brown, tergites 1–6 with anterior third light brown. Tergites 7–8 dark brown. Sternites brown. Posterior 4 segments of abdomen noticeably swollen relative to other segments (
<figureCitation box="[403,468,380,403]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1477,1496]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,777,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[151,1126,774,1456]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov.: 1 – male (Photo: J. Ševčík); 2 – female (Photo: J. Ševčík); 3 – male, habitus; 4 – female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,220,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis box="[144,260,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Terminalia</emphasis>
(Figs 9–12). Light brown, apex of gonostyli and medioventral lobe of sternite 9 darker. Sternite 9 sclerotized, medially covered with long setae, with medioventral lobe and a pair of lateroventral lobes, dark brown suture mediobasally. Medioventral lobe bare, as long as sternite 9, covering cerci, with two rounded processes bent ventrally and apical dark blunt bristles. Lateroventral lobe with bumpy margin, with several long setae and four dark apical megasetae. Tergite 9 sclerotized, densely covered with short setae and V-shaped indentation on the apex, bare transparent tapering part of base. Gonostyli bare, except lateral margin with long setae, dark blunt bristles on medial margin of apex, lateral rounded process and medial hooked process. Apex of gonostylus dark, tapering towards apex. Cerci and hypoproct covered with short trichia and long apical setae. Parameres strongly hooked at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,220,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,227,731,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[240,336,732,755]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1477,1496]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,777,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[151,1126,774,1456]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov.: 1 – male (Photo: J. Ševčík); 2 – female (Photo: J. Ševčík); 3 – male, habitus; 4 – female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
). Similar to male with following differences: antennal setae short, hind femur lighter with brown mark only anteriorly, genitalia lighter. Tergite 9 yellow, with long setae. Tergite 10 yellow, row of several long and shorter setae on posterior margin. Cerci brown, setose. Gonopore 9 brown. Gonocoxite 8 posteriorly brown and setose (
<figureCitation box="[961,1026,828,851]" captionStart="Figs 5–8. 5–7" captionStartId="3.[112,149,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-253@3.[115,1083,871,1529]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. 5–7 – Leptomorphus sevciki sp. nov., male: 5 – antennae; 6 – thorax, V-shape mark; 7 – wing; 8 – female, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315594/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
